
[1]espalier

   ESPAL'IER, n. [L. palus, a stake or pole.] A row of trees planted about
   a garden or in hedges, so as to inclose quarters or separate parts, and
   trained up to a lattice of wood-work, or fastened to stakes, forming a
   close hedge or shelter to protect plants against injuries from wind or
   weather.

   ESPAL'IER, v.t. To form an espalier, or to protect by an espalier.
